$ Oracle.DataAccess.Types.OracleBlob (class)

`Oracle.DataAccess.Types.OracleBlob` allows to access → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/data-types/lob[blob] data.

{ Writing blobs to files #ado-net-OracleBlob

  The following example tries to demonstrate how `OracleBlob` can be used to extract blob-data and write it into a file. The example assumes that there is a → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables[table] named `tableWithBlob` that has (at least) the two columns
 `filename` (a `varchar2`) and `image` with binary data to be stored in the file named `filename`.

  gh|.NET-API|/Oracle/DataAccess/Types/OracleBlob/writeBlobToFile.cs||

}

sa:
  A similar example for → development/databases/MySQL is → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/MySql/Data/MySqlClient/write-blob-to-file[here].

